strings:
<voice_0x01000DAD><se_low>King Trode: Oh, my poor castle!
It used to be so beautiful, but now it's in ruins.
<voice_0x01000DAE><se_low>King Trode: And it's all because of Dhoulmagus's evil curse.
<voice_0x01000DAF><se_low>King Trode: That's when our journey began, when the castle's secret treasure was plundered...

<voice_0x01000DB0><se_low>King Trode: Ah, there you are, Princess.
I know you like to look at the stars,
but it's a little chilly to be outside.
Perhaps you should retire to your chamber?

<voice_0x01000DB1><se_high>Princess Medea: Of course, Father.
I'll come right away.

<voice_0x01000DB2><se_low>King Trode: W-What's this!?
What's going on!?

<voice_0x01000DB3><se_high>Princess Medea: Hello? Is anybody there?
There's a man injured here.
Somebody please call a doctor!

<voice_0x01000DB4><se_low>King Trode: Speak to me! I command you!
Tell me what happened here!

<voice_0x01000DB5><se_def>*: Y-Your Majesty... S-Somebody...
 ...Th-The sealed chamber... Urgh.

<voice_0x01000DB6><se_low>King Trode: The sealed chamber!?
But surely no one would...!?

<voice_0x01000DB7><se_high>Princess Medea: Father, the intruder may still be up there.
It's too dangerous for you to go alone.

<voice_0x01000DB8><se_low>King Trode: Yes, but what if...
I can't just stand by and let someone steal it!

<voice_0x01000DB9><se_high>Princess Medea: I know.
So I'll go with you.

<voice_0x01000DBA><se_low>King Trode: Hm? I don't know...
Well, if there's no other alternative...

<voice_0x01000DBB><se_low>King Trode: You! What do you think you're doing!?
I forbid you to touch that sceptre!
<voice_0x01000DBC><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Why if it isn't King ‘Troll’ and Princess ‘Mare-dea’. I didn't expect you to find me...

<voice_0x01000DBD><se_def>Dhoulmagus: ...But what's done is done. Tell me,
is this sceptre as powerful as people say?
<voice_0x01000DBE><se_low>King Trode: You're that jester... You came to my castle so you could steal the sceptre!?
<voice_0x01000DBF><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Well deduced! You save me the bother of explaining myself, Your Majesty!
<voice_0x01000DC0><se_def>Dhoulmagus: I heard all about it.
<voice_0x01000DC1><se_def>Dhoulmagus: About a legendary magical sceptre sealed deep inside Castle Trodain. And about how it could bestow ultimate magical powers...
<voice_0x01000DC2><se_def>Dhoulmagus: With this, nothing can stop me from becoming the greatest magician of all time!
<voice_0x01000DC3><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Then I'll have my revenge on those scornful snobs who made a fool of me!

<voice_0x01000DC4><se_low>King Trode: Stop!
That sceptre must never leave this castle!

<voice_0x01000DC5><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Ha ha ha hah.
Nothing can stop me!

<voice_0x01000DC6><se_def>Dhoulmagus: I see no reason to delay this any further.
Time to unleash its true power...

<voice_0x01000DC7><se_def>Dhoulmagus: King Trode.
You will be my first guinea pig.
<voice_0x01000DC8><se_high>Princess Medea: Father, look out!
<voice_0x01000DC9><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Hm? Is that the best it can do?
<voice_0x01000DCA><se_def>Dhoulmagus: The mare I can see, but you look more like a toad than a troll to me!
<voice_0x01000DCB><se_def>Dhoulmagus: ...Ah, but wait! The magic circle here must be restricting its full powers.

<voice_0x01000DCC><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Ha ha ha. If I can take it away from here,
I'll see what it can really do!

<voice_0x01000DCD><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Come, precious sceptre!
Show me your true power!

<voice_0x01000DCE><se_def>Dhoulmagus: ...Oh yes! What incredible magic!
Perfect!

<voice_0x01000DCF><se_def>Dhoulmagus: S-So powerful...
I... I can't c-control it...
<voice_0x01000DD0><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Aaaaaargh!
<voice_0x01000DD1><se_low>King Trode: W-What on earth!?

<voice_0x01000DD2><se_def>Dhoulmagus: ......Ah! Ha ha ha hah.
Aha ha ha ha ha ha hah.
Ha! Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha haah.

<voice_0x01000DD3><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Hah! Wah ha ha ha hah!
Huh huh huh huh huh!
Kya ha ha ha hah!

<voice_0x01000DD4><se_low>King Trode: That day... We were inside the magic circle,
but you weren't. How did you manage to survive?

<voice_0x01000DD5><se_low>King Trode: ...Hm, who knows?
Maybe it was just luck.
You've always been a lucky one...
<voice_0x01000DD6><se_low>Yangus: Oi, guv! Wot are you an' the old codger jabberin' on about back there, eh!?

<voice_0x01000DD7><se_low>Yangus: Ain't we s'posed to be swottin' up on that ship?
Come on, get a move on!

<voice_0x01000DD8><se_low>King Trode: ...Ah, yes, of course.
The castle library should be just over there.
